# npx skills · Agent Skills (Best Practices)

This repository installs [Vercel Labs `agent-skills`](https://github.com/vercel-labs/agent-skills) via **`npx skills`**, and keeps the sources under **`.agents/skills/`**. Versions and sources are pinned with `skills-lock.json`.

## What the agent should do

- For **React / Next.js performance refactors and bundling** tasks, read **`.agents/skills/vercel-react-best-practices/SKILL.md`** before starting, and cite relevant `rules/*.md` files in the same folder when needed.
- For **component API design / boolean prop proliferation / composition patterns**, read **`.agents/skills/vercel-composition-patterns/SKILL.md`**.
- For **UI review / accessibility / web interface guidelines**, read **`.agents/skills/web-design-guidelines/SKILL.md`**.
- For **Vercel deployment** tasks, read **`.agents/skills/deploy-to-vercel/SKILL.md`**.
- For **Vercel CLI with access tokens** (non-interactive login), read **`.agents/skills/vercel-cli-with-tokens/SKILL.md`**.
- For **React Native / Expo** tasks, read **`.agents/skills/vercel-react-native-skills/SKILL.md`** (this repo is web-first; mobile is reference-only).

If there is a conflict with the repository's `.cursor/rules` (TypeScript style, performance, accessibility, etc.), prioritize the project rules and treat skills as **supporting references**.

## CLI (local)

- List: `npm run skills:list` (or `npx skills list`)
- Search: `npx skills find [keyword]`
- Re-install Vercel package (same skill set): `npm run skills:add:vercel`
- Update: `npm run skills:update`
- Restore from `skills-lock.json`: `npx skills experimental_install`

You can discover more skills at [https://skills.sh/](https://skills.sh/).

## Summary

Best practices live under **`.agents/skills/*/SKILL.md`** at the repository root. Read them first when starting work in that topic area.
